OL,3,CWhy UK drivers could face tougher
OL,4,Cpenalties for not wearing a seat belt
OL,6,FNot wearing a seat belt in cars could
OL,7,Ffinally land drivers and passengers
OL,8,Fwith penalty points on their license
OL,9,Fif the government gets public approval.
OL,11,FThe Department for Transport is
OL,12,Fcurrently running a consultation on
OL,13,Fwhether to enforce tougher penalties
OL,14,Ffor those who fail to buckle up.
OL,16,FIt became mandatory to wear one in the
OL,17,Ffront seat in 1983 while compulsory
OL,18,Frear-seat wearing cam into force in
OL,19,F1991.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
